      "comment": "BETTORSWEETVICTORY (7) led and saluted in a nice return to form at her most recent outing at this circuit and distance, getting home by 7 metres. Has to contend with a very wide draw but has the speed to get across so with even luck she could make it two on the trot. HAPPENSTBABEACHBOY (8) has been competitive from this line of late and kept the ball rolling last time when he came from this barrier for fifth at this circuit and distance. Should enjoy a trail and has the sprint lane to rely upon. Leading hope. WILD IDEAL (1) has come from wider barriers in each of her four starts this time in and has trialled since clocking in sixth here last time. Well served by the ace draw and should be ready to peak now. WILL HE REIGN (3) worked and faded last start but was racing consistently prior.",
